article.headline: Morgan St. 54, Delaware St. 40
article.story: DOVER, Del. (AP) -- Jamar Smith and Joseph McLean each scored 12 points, and Morgan State romped past Delaware State, 54-40, Monday night. Poor shooting doomed Delaware (12-11, 9-2 MEAC), and the loss ended a 22 home-game winning streak. "We lost because of a huge lack of effort. Our players did not come to play, they felt like Morgan was going to come in here and lay down," DSU head coach Greg Jackson said. Morgan (9-12, 7-3) shot 56.1 percent from the floor and outrebounded the Hornets 34-23. Aaron Fleetwood scored a team-high 12 points for DSU. Morgan State's win came two days after coach Todd Bozeman was charged with misdemeanor assault after an argument with a restaurant employee following a close loss.
